Sure! To write an if/then statement in C, you need to use the if keyword followed by a condition enclosed in parentheses. The statement within the curly braces ({}) will be executed if the condition is true. Here's an example:

```
if (age >= 18) {
  printf("You are eligible to vote.\n");
}
```

In this example, the if statement checks if the variable age is greater than or equal to 18. If the condition is true, the statement inside the curly braces will be executed, and the message "You are eligible to vote." will be printed on the screen.
